<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 01 at 3:29PM MDT  by NWS Pocatello</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Oneida
and southeastern Cassia Counties through 400 PM MDT...
At 328 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Juniper, or 18 miles west of Snowville, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Juniper.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
